<p>PathPlanner has been working great for us, except for one big issue I haven’t been able to solve.</p>
<p>I am unsure if this is a fundamental issue with PathPlanner, or if I am registering the Commands incorrectly. Whenever I run the L2 Named Command which is registered as:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">Commands.defer(() -&gt; 
                    Autos.ReefRoutine(drivetrain, visionSubsystem, elevatorSubsystem, intakeSubsystem, kX),
                    Set.of(drivetrain, visionSubsystem, elevatorSubsystem, intakeSubsystem))
</code></pre>
<p>After the Command ends the PathPlannerAuto Path does not continue afterwards, and the Command is unscheduled.</p>
<p>My current theory is that PathPlanner cannot handle the Pose changing when running a NamedCommand. If that’s the case how are other teams scoring in PathPlanner, and is there a work around?</p>
<p>If that’s not the issue than I must be doing something wrong somewhere, please help me out!</p>
